</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,258,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1587347119" country="Russia" location="Northern Europe" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" specimenCount="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,516,438,463]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Extra-limital distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="O.F.Müller, 1773" authorityName="Middendorff" authorityYear="1851" box="[527,646,438,463]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ectobranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[527,646,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">V. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
iS diStributed in 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03D787F9356BFFE51CF1EEE91149E1F6:8EA16034356BFFE51F30EFC71721E3FE" box="[854,1048,438,463]" country="Russia" name="Northern Europe" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Northern Europe</location>
weStward to ScandinaVia (
<bibRefCitation author="Gloer" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" refString="Gloer, P. (2002) Die SUßWassergastropoden Nord- Und MitteleUropas: BestimmUngschlUssel, LebenWeise, VerbreitUng. In: Die Tierwelt Deutschlands. Fol. 73. Conchbooks, Hackenheim, pp. 1 - 327." type="journal article" year="2002">Glöer 2002</bibRefCitation>
) and occurS throughout Siberia, being common in the partS of ASiatic 
<collectingCountry box="[988,1063,474,499]" name="Russia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">RuSSia</collectingCountry>
adjacent to 
<collectingCountry box="[1196,1305,474,499]" name="Mongolia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(ProzoroVa 
<emphasis box="[151,207,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">et al.</emphasis>
2009).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,258,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,546,571]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Variation.</emphasis>
Two conchologically diStinct formS of 
<taxonomicName authority="O.F.Müller, 1773" authorityName="Middendorff" authorityYear="1851" box="[757,870,546,571]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ectobranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[757,870,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">V. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be found in 
<collectingCountry box="[1054,1163,546,571]" name="Mongolia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
and Siberia. The typical form (See fig. 2 C) iS planiSpiral, with perfectly round aperture, and lacking the Spire. Another form, 
<taxonomicName authority="O.F.Müller, 1773" authorityName="Middendorff" authorityYear="1851" box="[1297,1412,582,607]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ectobranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[1297,1412,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">V. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
f. 
<emphasis box="[151,227,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">frigida</emphasis>
WeSterlund, 1873, iS characterized by Very low but diStinct Spire (See fig. 2 D). Some authorS (
<bibRefCitation author="ProzoroVa" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" refString="Prozorova, L. A. &amp; Starobogatov, Ya. I. (1998) SUbgenUs Sibirovalvata of the genUs Cincinna (Pectinibranchia Valvatidae) in RUssia and adjacent area. The Bulletin of the Russian Far East Malacological Society, 2, 54 - 74. [in RUssian]" type="journal article" year="1998">ProzoroVa &amp; StarobogatoV 1998</bibRefCitation>
; StarobogatoV 
<emphasis box="[534,583,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">et al</emphasis>
. 2004) accept the latter form aS a Valid SpecieS but a recent molecular Study by Clewing 
<emphasis box="[288,337,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">et al</emphasis>
. (2014) haS not reVealed any genetic differenceS between it and the typical form of 
<taxonomicName authority="O.F.Müller, 1773" authorityName="Middendorff" authorityYear="1851" box="[1274,1387,690,715]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ectobranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[1274,1387,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">V. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,258,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,726,751]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Remark.</emphasis>
The Subgeneric placement of 
<taxonomicName authority="O.F.Müller, 1773" authorityName="Middendorff" authorityYear="1851" box="[639,751,726,751]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ectobranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[639,751,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">V. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
waS the matter of diScrepancieS. StarobogatoV &amp; 
<bibRefCitation pageId="8" pageNumber="53" refString="Starobogatov, Ya. I. &amp; Streletzkaja, E. A. (1967) Composition and zoogeographical characteristics of freshWater malacofaUna of the East Siberia and northern part of the Far East. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Soviet Academy of Sciences, 42, 221 - 268. [in RUssian]" type="journal article">Streletzkaja (1967)</bibRefCitation>
and all SubSequent RuSSian authorS claSSified it within the SubgenuS 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Starobogatov &amp; Streletzkaja" authorityYear="1967" box="[1044,1194,762,787]" class="Gastropoda" family="Gastropoda (awaiting allocation)" genus="Sibirovalvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gastropoda (awaiting allocation)" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1044,1194,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Sibirovalvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<bibRefCitation author="Gloer" box="[1286,1436,762,787]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" refString="Gloer, P. (2002) Die SUßWassergastropoden Nord- Und MitteleUropas: BestimmUngschlUssel, LebenWeise, VerbreitUng. In: Die Tierwelt Deutschlands. Fol. 73. Conchbooks, Hackenheim, pp. 1 - 327." type="journal article" year="2002">Glöer (2002)</bibRefCitation>
conSidered it aS a member of the SubgenuS 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Adams" authorityYear="1854" box="[678,787,798,823]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Tropidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[678,787,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Tropidina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
H. et A. AdamS, 1854, with the 
<typeStatus box="[1198,1246,799,823]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">type</typeStatus>
SpecieS 
<taxonomicName authority="(Say, 1817)" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1817" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1817" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ectobranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tricarinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Valvata tricarinata</emphasis>
(Say, 1817)
</taxonomicName>
inhabiting North America. Clewing 
<emphasis box="[827,876,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">et al</emphasis>
. (2014) haVe Shown that SpecimenS of 
<taxonomicName authority="O.F.Müller, 1773" authorityName="Middendorff" authorityYear="1851" box="[1322,1435,834,859]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ectobranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[1322,1435,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">V. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[288,379,871,895]" country="American Samoa" name="Western" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">WeStern</collectingRegion>
Siberia demonStrate more tight affinity to the Northern American ValVatidS than to 
<taxonomicName authority="WeSterlund, 1897" authorityName="WeSterlund" authorityYear="1897" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ectobranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis box="[1321,1436,871,895]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">V. confusa</emphasis>
WeSterlund, 1897
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[416,464,907,931]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">type</typeStatus>
SpecieS of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Starobogatov &amp; Streletzkaja" authorityYear="1967" box="[603,753,906,931]" class="Gastropoda" family="Gastropoda (awaiting allocation)" genus="Sibirovalvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gastropoda (awaiting allocation)" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[603,753,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Sibirovalvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It meanS that the placement of 
<taxonomicName authority="O.F.Müller, 1773" authorityName="Middendorff" authorityYear="1851" box="[1142,1260,906,931]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ectobranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[1142,1260,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">V. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Adams" authorityYear="1854" box="[1326,1435,906,931]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Tropidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1326,1435,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Tropidina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
propoSed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gloer" box="[295,441,942,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" refString="Gloer, P. (2002) Die SUßWassergastropoden Nord- Und MitteleUropas: BestimmUngschlUssel, LebenWeise, VerbreitUng. In: Die Tierwelt Deutschlands. Fol. 73. Conchbooks, Hackenheim, pp. 1 - 327." type="journal article" year="2002">Glöer (2002)</bibRefCitation>
iS more correct.
</paragraph>
